DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(84)90014-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439328490014X
AB  - The effect of deposit rate regulation on bank solvency is an important and unresolved issue that has received only limited attention. In this paper, capital market data is used to assess changes in both systematic and non-systematic risk of a portfolio of bank stocks at the time of deposit rate deregulation. The evidence indicates that neither measure of capital market risk is significantly affected, leading to the conclusion that bank solvency risk will not be increased by the deregulation of interest rates on deposits.
